<subSubSection lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="25.[151,1436,1908,2043]" lastBlockId="26.[151,1437,150,645]" lastPageId="26" lastPageNumber="427" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1980,2006]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Remarks.</emphasis>
This specimen from Kermadec Islands belongs to the group of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[1016,1251,1980,2006]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1016,1251,1980,2006]" italics="true" pageId="25" pageNumber="426">Leptochiton belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as characterized by 
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I." box="[186,357,2016,2043]" pageId="25" pageNumber="426" pagination="151 - 202" refId="ref19002" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptochiton Gray, 1847 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4033.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko (2015)</bibRefCitation>
. The sculpture and shape of the valves of the present specimen are very similar to the description of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Iredale &amp; Hull" baseAuthorityYear="1925" box="[182,313,151,176]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="opiparus">
<emphasis box="[182,313,151,176]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. opiparus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
given by Iredale &amp; Hull (1925). The current identification is tentative as a conclusive decision will only be possible after a detailed study of the nominal species. The present specimen has 13 gills on both sides. The whole tegmentum is sculptured with small quincuncially arranged granules. Each granule has five aesthetes. The dorsal girdle scales show several very weak riblets. The radula has a broad central tooth and a unidentate cusp of the major lateral tooth with a very small rudiment of an inner denticle. The specimen differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[1195,1319,295,321]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[1195,1319,295,321]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having five aesthetes in each granule (vs. three in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[625,750,331,357]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[625,750,331,357]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), several very weak riblets at the dorsal girdle scales (vs. 1–3 distinct ribs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Dall" authorityYear="1878" box="[318,444,367,393]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="belknapi">
<emphasis box="[318,444,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. belknapi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
The specimen from Kermadec is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2015" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[686,991,402,429]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sigwartae">
<emphasis box="[686,826,403,428]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. sigwartae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I." box="[833,991,402,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" pagination="151 - 202" refId="ref19002" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptochiton Gray, 1847 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4033.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Sirenko, 2015" authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[1045,1370,402,429]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mutschkeae">
<emphasis box="[1045,1206,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. mutschkeae</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sirenko, B. I." box="[1213,1370,402,429]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" pagination="151 - 202" refId="ref19002" refString="Sirenko, B. I. (2015) Shallow and deep-sea chitons of the genus Leptochiton Gray, 1847 (Mollusca: Polyplacophora: Lepidopleurida) from Peruvian and Chilean waters. Zootaxa, 4033 (2), 151 - 202. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4033.2.1" type="journal article" year="2015">Sirenko, 2015</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(both from off 
<collectingCountry box="[250,312,439,466]" name="Chile" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">Chile</collectingCountry>
) but differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[508,647,439,464]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sigwartae">
<emphasis box="[508,647,439,464]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. sigwartae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a convex anterior margin of intermediate valve (vs. concave in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[180,320,475,500]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sigwartae">
<emphasis box="[180,320,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. sigwartae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), wide dorsal girdle scales with several very weak riblets (narrow scales with two distinct ribs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sigwartae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. sigwartae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), the head valve wider than the tail valve (vs. head valve narrower than tail valve in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[1209,1349,511,536]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="sigwartae">
<emphasis box="[1209,1349,511,536]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. sigwartae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="26.[151,1437,150,645]" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">
The Kermadec specimen differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[625,785,547,573]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mutschkeae">
<emphasis box="[625,785,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. mutschkeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having a major lateral tooth with a big, unicuspid head with a very small rudiment of an inner denticle (vs. without rudiment at inner edge in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[1116,1277,583,609]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mutschkeae">
<emphasis box="[1116,1277,583,609]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. mutschkeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), several very weak riblets in dorsal girdle scales (vs. 2 ribs in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Sirenko" authorityYear="2015" box="[692,852,619,645]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Leptochitonidae" genus="Leptochiton" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidopleurida" pageId="26" pageNumber="427" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="mutschkeae">
<emphasis box="[692,852,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="427">L. mutschkeae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
